  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb 04\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0dd4. 500,000\u0d9a \u0daf\u0da9\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "04 eggs for Rs. 500,000 fine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Balangoda Acting Magistrate A. ordered to pay a fine of 500,000 rupees to a vendor in Balangoda town who sold 4 white eggs at a price of 260 rupees at a higher price than the prescribed price for eggs. Amy. S. Mrs. Menike ordered last (28).",
        "The fine amount had to be paid to Cope City Trading Company, which is controlled by the Balangoda Various Services Cooperative Society. According to the gazette announcement issued by the Consumer Affairs Authority on the 19th, the maximum retail price that can be sold for a white egg is 43 rupees.",
        "According to that, during the raids conducted in Balangoda city, the price of eggs was taken from those markets by a strategist and an amount of 260 rupees was charged for four eggs at 65 rupees per egg, the officials of the consumer authority said.",
        "Balangoda Acting Magistrate A.M.S. Mrs. Menike fixed the fine amount of five lakhs as follows.",
        "According to the instructions of Ratnapura Consumer Authority District Head Mr. Udaya Namalgama, the officers Nasik Ahmed and Nadisha Liyanage were present for this raid organized by the investigation officer Mrs. Harshani Dasanayake."
      ],
